          "correct": "mode=='highest' ? (E[i]==max(E)) : (mode=='lowest' ? (E[i]==min(E)) : (mode=='differs' ? (count([E[0]==E[i],E[1]==E[i],E[2]==E[i],E[3]==E[i]])==1) : (count([E[0]==E[i],E[1]==E[i],E[2]==E[i],E[3]==E[i]])>=2)))",
          "label": "'Option ' + names[i]",
          "why": "'EMV = ' + ks[i]*10 + '%×$' + (E[i]+(10-ks[i])*ts[i]) + 'k + ' + (100-ks[i]*10) + '%×$' + (E[i]-ks[i]*ts[i]) + 'k = $' + E[i] + 'k' + (mode=='highest' ? (E[i]==max(E) ? ' — the highest.' : ' — not the highest.') : (mode=='lowest' ? (E[i]==min(E) ? ' — the lowest.' : ' — not the lowest.') : (mode=='differs' ? (count([E[0]==E[i],E[1]==E[i],E[2]==E[i],E[3]==E[i]])==1 ? ' — the odd one out.' : ' — shares this EMV with others.') : (count([E[0]==E[i],E[1]==E[i],E[2]==E[i],E[3]==E[i]])>=2 ? ' — matches another branch.' : ' — a unique EMV.'))))"
        }
      ]
    },
    "explanation": "Each branch's EMV is the probability-weighted average of its payoffs. {{mode=='differs' ? 'Three branches share an EMV; the fourth is the odd one out.' : (mode=='same' ? 'Two branches share an EMV even though their probabilities and payoffs look different.' : (mode=='highest' ? 'The largest weighted average wins.' : 'The smallest weighted average is the answer.'))}}"
